<dl id="n34034g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n34" href="#n34034g">N34 (VI.B.27)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n34all.htm#n34034g"> 34(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> a<sup>0</sup> = 1</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The logarithm of 1 is 0. For <i>a</i><sup>0</sup> = 1 for all values of<i>a</i>; therefore log 1 = 0, whatever the base may be. <small> Hall &amp; Knight, <a name="HSHK" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#HSHK"><cite title="source">Elementary Algebra for Schools</cite></a> (n.d) 341</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
